    "text": "This is just lifting — keep training as planned, no rest day required. Heavy legs the day after a solid leg session is the expected bill, and your systemic markers say the rest of you is fine: recovery is 71%, HRV is 66 ms against a 65.1 ms baseline, and your resting heart rate is 54 bpm, matching its usual level. What you felt is local muscular fatigue, and an easy run is actually one of the better responses to it — blood flow without much new damage — as long as you genuinely keep the effort conversational and let the pace be whatever it is. One concrete adjustment: if the legs still feel like bricks tomorrow, push your next quality session back a day rather than forcing it. Rest days are for systemic fatigue; this is the local kind that easy movement handles well.",
